cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a method for learning conditional correlations among multiple entities using deep neural networks and applies it to two real-world applications in computational sustainability. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), or cryptography and security (cs.CR). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a learning scheme that integrates with deep neural networks. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for capturing correlation structures among exponentially many outcomes. Computer vision (cs.CV) is relevant as one of the applications involves modeling multi-dimensional landscape composition and human footprint in the Amazon rainforest with satellite images. Natural language processing (cs.CL) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) are less likely as they are not directly related to the content of the paper.
